\section*{5. Advanced Visualization Framework}
\subsection*{3D Geospatial Dashboard}
The system provides an interactive 3D visualization platform using modern web technologies:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{CesiumJS Integration:} High-performance 3D globe rendering with geological overlays
    \item \textbf{Leaflet 3D:} Lightweight 3D mapping with borehole cross-section visualization
    \item \textbf{Kepler.gl:} GPU-accelerated geospatial visualization for large datasets
    \item \textbf{WebGL Rendering:} Hardware-accelerated 3D geological modeling and probability mapping
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{Visualization Outputs}
The dashboard generates multiple visualization layers:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Gold Probability Heatmaps:} Interactive probability surfaces with uncertainty bounds
    \item \textbf{Borehole Cross-Sections:} 3D subsurface visualization of lithology and gold concentrations
    \item \textbf{Geological Feature Maps:} Segmented geological units from Phase 1 EarthScape models
    \item \textbf{Temporal Analysis:} Time-series visualization of model predictions and validations
    \item \textbf{Exploration Decision Support:} Interactive tools for targeting high-probability zones
\end{enumerate}

\subsection*{Technical Implementation}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{FastAPI Backend:} RESTful API for serving model predictions and borehole data
    \item \textbf{WebSocket Updates:} Real-time model updates and validation results
    \item \textbf{Progressive Web App:} Offline-capable interface for field exploration teams
\end{itemize}

